 all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Heleigh was born about 1403, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Heleigh. He had at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1403–":"umbes 1403–Surnud","1403–Male":"1403–Surnud","1427–1475":"1427–1475","1430–1458":"1430–1458","–Male":"Surnud","1458":"1458","1403":"1403","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","Abt 1403":"umbes 1403","1427":"1427","Of Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1403–":"noin 1403–Kuollut","1403–Male":"1403–Kuollut","1427–1475":"1427–1475","1430–1458":"1430–1458","–Male":"Kuollut","1458":"1458","1403":"1403","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","Abt 1403":"noin 1403","1427":"1427","Of Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1403–":"environ 1403–Décédé","1403–Male":"1403–Décédé","1427–1475":"1427–1475","1430–1458":"1430–1458","–Male":"Décédé","1458":"1458","1403":"1403","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","Abt 1403":"environ 1403","1427":"1427","Of Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir William Heleigh est né environ 1403, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de John Heleigh. Il a eu au moins 2 filles."},"de":{"Abt 1403–":"um 1403–Verstorben","1403–Male":"1403–Verstorben","1427–1475":"1427–1475","1430–1458":"1430–1458","–Male":"Verstorben","1458":"1458","1403":"1403","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","Abt 1403":"um 1403","1427":"1427","Of Ches